<title>The Zen of Facilitation Poem</title>

</head>

<body>
	<h1>Zen Facilitation</h1>
	<p>By Benjamin Theisen</p>
<br>
<p>March 22, 2017</p>
<br>
<p>The greatest achievement</p>
	<ul>Awaits your creation</ul>
<p>Making it easy</p>
	<ul>With facilitation</ul>
<p>To push or to pull</p>
	<ul>In new situations</ul>
<p>Yielding and guiding</p>
	<ul>Without expectations</ul>
<br>
<p>Should a fistfight break out</p>
	<ul>Don't play referee</ul>
<p>Don't be Bruce Lee</p>
	<ul>Think of safety</ul>
<p>The zen of the question</p>
	<ul>That gets nothing back</ul>
<p>Silence so pointed</p>
	<ul>You'd welcome a laugh</ul>
<br>
<p>You may not get hecklers</p>
	<ul>But you'll see a shade</ul>
<p>Of sidebar discussions</p>
	<ul>At whispering range</ul>
<p>If you can be subtle</p>
	<ul>I hope indirect</ul>
<p>Standing beside them</p>
	<ul>Can garner respect</ul>
<br>
<p>You need not confront<p>
	<ul>Or disrupt the zen flow</ul>
<p>Maintain the balance<p>
	<ul>And guide them in tow</ul>
<p>Heeding advice from</p>
	<ul>The masters of zen</ul>
<p>Be empty and open</p>
	<ul>A vessel for them</ul>
<br>
<p>Sometimes you're the star</p>
	<ul>Who lights up the room</ul>
<p>Sometimes you're the moon</p>
	<ul>Who hovers and looms</ul>
<p>For me, the best outcome</p>
	<ul>Is when I'm prepared</ul>
<p>"Great meeting," they said</p>
	<ul>And forgot I was there</ul>
<br>
<p>The zen master pulls</p>
	<ul>On the great wooden bow</ul>
<p>The arrows all land</p>
	<ul>Where they needed to go</ul>
</body>
